docs.text: \[ \operatorname{ker} f=\{g\in G:f(g)=e_{H}\}{\mbox{.}} \] The homomorphism \(f\) is injective if and only if its kernel is only the singleton set \(e_G\) , because otherwise \(\exists a,b\in G\) with \(a\neq b\) such that \(f(a)=f(b)\) .
